Dc Museums.MuseumName: Smithsonian National Museum of Natural History
Dc Museums.MuseumDescription: Established in 1910 and located on the National Mall, this prestigious museum, part of the Smithsonian Institution, holds the world's most extensive collection of natural history specimens and human artifacts including the remains of dinosaurs and tools used by early man.
Dc Museums.MuseumAddress: 10th St. & Constitution Ave. NW, Washington, DC 20560
